# EOL-DRIFT-1 (slice-033 / ADR-033): the byte-equality-guarded `.md` surface
# is pinned to LF so Windows core.autocrlf=true checkouts do not re-acquire
# the R-5 CRLF false-FAIL. The shared EOL-agnostic comparator
# (tests/skill_drift_equality.py) is the environment-independent correctness
# fix; this file is the durability layer + keeps `git status` clean.
# Scope is deliberately narrow (the guarded surface only) — whole-vault
# renormalization is explicitly out of slice-033 scope.
skills/**/SKILL.md text eol=lf
skills/diagnose/passes/*.md text eol=lf
agents/*.md text eol=lf
